0the%20case%20to%20protect%20other%20artists%20for%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20done%20nothing%20more%20than%20write%20a%20song.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrake-kendrick-lamar-beef-explained-timeline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDrake%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20his%20own%20label%2C%20UMG%20Recordings%2C%20Inc.%2C%20amid%20his%20ongoing%20beef%20with%20Kendrick%20Lamar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rapper%2C%20whose%20full%20name%20is%20Aubrey%20Drake%20Graham%2C%20accused%20Universal%20Music%20Group%20of%20approving%20and%20publishing%20Lamar's%20diss%20track%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkendrick-lamar-not-like-us-music-video-drake-references-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BNot%20Like%20Us%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20the%20complaint%20says%20includes%20allegations%20that%20UMG%20%26quot%3Bunderstood%20were%20not%20only%20false%2C%20but%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20song%20%26quot%3Bfalsely%20accuses%20Drake%20of%20being%20a%20pedophile%20and%20calls%20for%20violent%20retribution%20against%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit%20filed%20in%20the%20US%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20UMG%20enriched%20itself%20and%20its%20shareholders%20by%20exploiting%20Drake's%20music%20for%20years%2C%20and%20knew%20that%20the%20salacious%20allegations%20against%20Drake%20were%20false%2C%20UMG%20chose%20corporate%20greed%20over%20the%20safety%20and%20well-being%20of%20its%20artists%2C%26quot%3B%20Drake%2C%20through%20his%20attorneys%2C%20stated%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Drake%20and%20UMG%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUMG%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20that%20it%20intends%20to%20fight%20the%20lawsuit%20to%20protect%20other%20artists%20for%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20done%20nothing%20more%20than%20write%20a%20song.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20pointed%20to%20one%20incident%20in%20May%20in%20which%20someone%20opened%20fire%20outside%20his%20Toronto%20home%2C%20striking%20the%20front%20door%20and%20wounding%20a%20security%20guard%2C%20who%20the%20lawsuit%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20Drake's%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20days%20following%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said%20there%20were%20two%20attempted%20break-ins%20at%20his%20property%2C%20one%20of%20which%20involved%20an%20individual%20who%20dug%20under%20the%20property's%20gate%20with%20his%20bare%20hands%20and%20%26quot%3Bmanaged%20to%20yell%20racist%20slurs%20and%20threats%20against%20Drake%20before%20being%20escorted%20off%20the%20property.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20underscored%20that%20Lamar%20was%20not%20named%20as%20a%20defendant.%20It%20said%20UMG's%20actions%20in%20publishing%20the%20track%20were%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20string%20of%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20further%20said%20that%20UMG%20did%20not%20help%20Drake%20when%20he%20confronted%20company%20executives%20about%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20is%20another%20escalation%20in%20the%20ongoing%20beef%20between%20two%20chart-topping%20rappers%20that%20started%20more%20than%2010%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20began%20as%20an%20exchange%20of%20subtle%20shots%20and%20coded%20lyrics%20in%20their%20songs%20turned%20into%20an%20all-out%20musical%20brawl%20last%20year%20after%20Lamar%20once%20again%20declared%20himself%20the%20king%20of%20hip-hop%20in%20a%20collaborative%20track%20with%20rapper%20Future%20and%20producer%20Metro%20Boomin.%20In%20the%20song%2C%20he%20directly%20responded%20to%20Drake's%202023%20track%2C%20%26quot%3BFirst%20Person%20Shooter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20month%2C%20Drake%20and%20Lamar%20exchanged%20several%20searing%20diss%20trac